@BrianMitchellMP Thank you!! I hope something can be done soon for the indefinitely separated life partners & families due to the borders too. My life partner is a foreigner and pretty much my only family, so it’s been a very lonely 11 months without him by my side now.

I live alone. I’m now on jobseeker. I have a mental illness. I have social anxiety. I haven’t seen family in months. I was built for COVID-19. I’m thriving because I  finally have the time to look after my mental health. I feel stronger than ever. #qanda

@GregHuntMP Virginian isn't speaking for all of us... The roadmap and the numbers going down have significantly eased my anxiety. My mental health has  improved dramatically as a result. Speaking to family and friends many of them feel this way too.
